  "response": "There are several highly regarded English translations of the Bhagavad Gita. Some of the most respected and considered authentic include:\n\n1. Swami Prabhupada's translation (ISKCON version)\n- Widely known and popular\n- Follows Vaishnava philosophical tradition\n- Includes detailed commentary\n\n2. Eknath Easwaran's translation\n- Considered scholarly and accessible\n- Provides cultural and philosophical context\n- Known for clear and readable prose\n\n3. Dr. Radhakrishnan's translation\n- Highly academic and philosophically deep\n- Provides extensive philosophical commentary\n- Respected in scholarly circles\n\n4. Juan Mascaro's translation\n- Poetic and lyrical approach\n- Emphasizes spiritual essence\n- Appreciated for its literary quality\n\n5. Swami Sivananda's translation\n- Comprehensive with detailed explanations\n- Follows traditional Advaita Vedanta interpretation\n- Includes extensive commentaries\n\nThe \"most authentic\" can be subjective and depends on individual perspective, philosophical tradition, and personal interpretation. Scholars and spiritual practitioners often recommend reading multiple translations to gain a comprehensive understanding.\n\nFor serious study, comparing multiple translations and consulting original Sanskrit commentaries is recommended.",
